Bernard Frederick was a Welsh professional rugby league footballer of the 1910s, playing at representative level for Wales, and at club level for Oldham, as a Loose forward/Lock, i.e. number 13, in the era of contested scrums.[1] Bernard Frederick won a cap for Wales while at Oldham in 1913.[2]
